The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Sunday, March 20, 2005 

 Cannabis rules

 London, March 19 (Reuters): The British government said today it had asked for an assessment of its decision to ease the rules on cannabis after studies showed the drug?s use may be linked to mental health problems.

 Home secretary Charles Clarke, a year after his predecessor controversially re-classified the drug, has asked a statutory public body to review the downgrade to a relatively low risk C category. 




